paces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Dario Amodei</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Susie Wiles</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Scott Bessent</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">David O Sacks</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/04/multimedia/00biz-trump-ai-jtvh/00biz-trump-ai-jtvh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Salwan Georges for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The Trump administration’s shift in policy began after Anthropic introduced a powerful artificial intelligence model called Mythos. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>American Factories Lag in Adopting A.I. This Drugmaker Is an Exception.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/business/ai-bristol-myers-squibb-drugs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/business/ai-bristol-myers-squibb-drugs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/business/ai-bristol-myers-squibb-drugs.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A Bristol Myers Squibb plant that makes cancer drugs was the only manufacturer in the U.S. recognized for innovation by the World Economic Forum this year.</description><dc:creator>Farah Stockman</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 09:02:03 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pharmaceuticals</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">prescription drugs</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Manufacturing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cancer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Bristol Myers Squibb</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Davos World Economic Forum</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Clinical trial</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Research</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Massachusetts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/05/multimedia/00biz-ai-drug-factory-01-bgtq/00biz-ai-drug-factory-01-bgtq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Sophie Park for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>At the Bristol Myers Squibb facility in Devens, Mass., scientists use automated machines to help make cancer drugs. </media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Elon Musk’s Confidante Shivon Zilis Is Cast as His Inside Source at OpenAI</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/elon-musk-shivon-zilis-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/elon-musk-shivon-zilis-openai-trial.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" h