eral trial on Wednesday.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Elon Musk Wanted OpenAI to Go Commercial, Greg Brockman Testifies</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/05/technology/openai-trial-elon-musk-greg-brockman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/05/technology/openai-trial-elon-musk-greg-brockman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/05/technology/openai-trial-elon-musk-greg-brockman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Greg Brockman, OpenAI’s president, testified in a trial pitting Mr. Musk against his company that the world’s richest man was eager to change how it operated as a nonprofit.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz and Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 21:58:33 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Nonprofit</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Sam Altman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Greg Brockman</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/05/multimedia/05biz-ai-trial-ledeall-01-wbjz/05biz-ai-trial-ledeall-01-wbjz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jason Henry for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI’s president, Greg Brockman, with his wife, Anna Brockman, at the federal courthouse in Oakland, Calif., on Tuesday. He testified for a second day.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Meditating or Rebooting? A Robot Buddhist Monk Comes to South Korea.</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/06/technology/robot-monk-buddhist-seoul.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Gabi, the newest monk at a temple in Seoul that is looking to spread Buddhism, vowed to not overcharge as it seeks enlightenment.</description><dc:creator>Remy Tumin and John Yoon</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 21:21:45 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Buddhism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Monasteries</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jogye</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Robot</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Seoul</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/06/world/asia/2026-05-06T054951Z_2010695814_RC2H3LARFX6Z_RTRMADP_3_SOUTHKOREA-ROBOT-MONK/2026-05-06T054951Z_2010695814_RC2H3LARFX6Z_RTRMADP_3_SOUTHKOREA-ROBOT-MONK-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Yonhap News Agency, via via Reuters</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Ford Says an Affordable Electric Pickup Truck is Still Coming Next Year</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/05/business/ford-motor-electric-pickup-truck.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss